evidence: one of the most important habits in MATLAB programming
Instead of looping through each element one by one
apply an operation to the whole array at once
Same result, much faster, much cleaner.
Because Matlab is an interpreted language, i.e., it is not compiled before execution, loops run slowly.
Vectorized code runs faster in Matlab.
Whenever you can, avoid loops. Use vectorized operations. MATLAB is built for that.

concepts.term: Whenever you can, avoid loops. Use vectorized operations. MATLAB is built for that.
